%bridge-context: REVERSE Drury (2C); Opener's 2D rebid = light 3rd-seat opening
{Bold bidders might have opened with this hand, so when partner opens in third seat you naturally want to show your strength. If you play Reverse Drury there is only one way to do that, so you bid 2\C.

Partner rebids 2\D. What do you say next? 

The 2\D rebid shows a hand that partner would have opened in any position. So here it gets a little ambiguous. Surely a jump to 3\S would be forcing, but to keep the possibility of misunderstandings low a jump to 4\S is no doubt safer. After all, you can revalue your hand up to 13 points in support of \Ss.}

